---
/**
 * Chatbot climax — the differentiator's payoff, placed late (before Contact) after
 * the persistent launcher has been inviting all the way down. Shell + invitation
 * only: the conversational backend is a future change, so this shows an explicit
 * "coming soon" state, never a broken or erroring conversation UI.
 */
---

<section class="section section--scene section--stack bot" id="chatbot" aria-label="Ask the assistant">
  <div class="section__inner bot__inner">
    <p class="kicker" data-reveal>Beyond the CV</p>
    <h2 class="bot__head" data-reveal>Don't just read — <em>talk.</em></h2>
    <p class="bot__sub" data-reveal>
      An assistant that knows the reasoning, not just the résumé — my pipelines, my
      architecture, the trade-offs behind each decision. Ask it what a CV can't tell you.
    </p>

    <!-- Faux composer: clearly inert, labelled coming soon (no dead/erroring UI). -->
    <div class="bot__composer" data-reveal aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="bot__placeholder">Ask about my Databricks work…</span>
      <span class="bot__badge">Coming soon</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .bot { text-align: left; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
  /* Wider block so the copy breathes (the sub-line reads as ~2 lines, not a
     cramped column). The scene now sits more behind the text — by design. */
  .bot__inner { max-width: 62rem; }
  .bot__head {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 400;
    /* Bumped up a step; still one line on desktop within the wider block. */
    font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 5.8vw, 4.6rem); line-height: 0.95;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-dim); margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 40rem) { .bot__head { white-space: nowrap; } }
  /* "talk." carries the gold accent (the CTA word), tying it to the Talk launcher. */
  .bot__head em { color: var(--gold); font-style: normal; }
  .bot__sub {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.6vw, 1.7rem); line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink-dim); max-width: 58rem; margin-bottom: clamp(1.8rem, 4vh, 2.6rem);
  }

  /* Glass input bar — THE single gold beat of this section: a clear-glass pill
     ringed and lit in gold so the eye lands on the invitation, not the copy. */
  .bot__composer {
    box-sizing: border-box; /* so max-width is the TOTAL width (aligns the right edge) */
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--gold); border-radius: 999px;
    background:
      var(--glass-sheen),
      linear-gradient(var(--glass-dim), var(--glass-dim));
    backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur)) saturate(1.05);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur)) saturate(1.05);
    /* Stronger gold glow — the moody ghost-button feel from the ref. */
    box-shadow: 0 0 38px rgba(224, 163, 62, 0.40), inset 0 0 16px rgba(224, 163, 62, 0.14);
    /* Match the widest text line above so their right edges align. */
    max-width: 54.5rem;
  }
  .bot__placeholder { font-family: var(--font-body); color: var(--ink-faint); }
  /* Quiet "coming soon" — no gold (scarcity rule); a plain ink/line chip. */
  .bot__badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-dim);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px;
    flex: none;
  }
</style>
